This paper deals with the problem of approximating surfaces in 3D space by meshes, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the regularity of the generated meshes, which is a topic of interest in computer graphics (cs.GR). The algorithms presented in the paper involve numerical optimization, which falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques for mesh generation, which could potentially fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) or computer vision (cs.CV). Overall, cs.CG and cs.GR are the most likely categories, followed by cs.NA, cs.MM, and cs.CV.
